CSS Flexbox is a one-dimensional layout method for arranging items in rows or columns.

## Flexbox Fundamentals
```css
.container {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    align-items: center;
}
```

## Properties
- flex-direction, justify-content, align-items, flex-wrap, gap

CSS Grid is a two-dimensional layout system for creating complex page layouts.

## Getting Started
```css
.container {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 20px;
}
```

## Common Patterns
Holy Grail layout, card grids, responsive without media queries.

