The aggregation pipeline processes data through stages.

## Basic Pipeline
```javascript
const pipeline = [
    { $match: { status: 'active' } },
    { $group: { _id: '$category', total: { $sum: '$amount' } } },
    { $sort: { total: -1 } },
    { $limit: 10 }
];

const results = await db.collection('orders').aggregate(pipeline).toArray();
```

## Common Stages

### $match (Filter)
```javascript
{ $match: { age: { $gte: 18 }, city: 'New York' } }
```

### $group (Grouping)
```javascript
{ $group: { _id: '$department', avgSalary: { $avg: '$salary' }, count: { $sum: 1 } } }
```

### $project (Field Selection)
```javascript
{ $project: { name: 1, email: 1, age: 1, _id: 0 } }
```

### $sort (Ordering)
```javascript
{ $sort: { createdAt: -1, name: 1 } }
```

### $lookup (Join)
```javascript
{
  $lookup: {
    from: 'orders',
    localField: '_id',
    foreignField: 'userId',
    as: 'orders'
  }
}
```

## Example: Sales Report
```javascript
const salesReport = await db.collection('orders').aggregate([
    { $match: { date: { $gte: startDate, $lte: endDate } } },
    { $group: { _id: { $dateToString: { format: '%Y-%m-%d', date: '$date' } }, totalSales: { $sum: '$amount' }, orderCount: { $sum: 1 } } },
    { $sort: { _id: 1 } },
    { $project: { date: '$_id', totalSales: 1, orderCount: 1, _id: 0 } }
]).toArray();
```

The aggregation pipeline is MongoDB's most powerful feature for data analysis.

